{{Orphan|date=November 2015}} {{Infobox criminal | name = Hakim Marnissi | birth_date = 1990 | residence = Toulon, France | criminal_charge = Criminal association with a terrorist enterprise }}
The '''Hakim Marnissi Case''' is an investigation into a [[France|French]] [[radical Islam|Islamist radical]], Hakim Marnissi, for an attempted attack on the [[naval base]] of [[Toulon]]. He was arrested 29 October 2015 after receiving a hood and combat knife with integrated [[brass knuckles]] via mail order. Marnissi was indicted on 2 November for [[criminal association]] with a [[terrorist group|terrorist enterprise]] and imprisoned.<ref name="figaro">{{Cite web|author = Christophe Cornevin|title= Attentat déjoué à Toulon : le profil du commanditaire se précise|url = http://www.lefigaro.fr/actualite-france/2015/11/10/01016-20151110ARTFIG00433-un-attentat-contre-des-militaires-dejoue-a-toulon.php|work = Le Figaro|archive-date= 10 November 2015|access-date = 11 November 2015}}</ref>
In the summer of 2014, Marnissi came to the attention of the [[General Directorate for Internal Security|DGSI]] when he started posting [[Facebook]] messages of support to volunteer [[jihadi|fighters]] in the Syrian-Iraqi combat who were under the banner of [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant|Daech]]. While monitoring Marnissi, the police intercepted several emails exchanged directly with French jihadists currently fighting in Syria.<ref name="tf1">{{cite news|author=Gilles Bouleau|date=11 November 2015|title=Attentat déjoué à Toulon : ce que l’on sait du plan prévu par Hakim Marnissi|url=http://lci.tf1.fr/jt-20h/videos/2015/attentat-dejoue-a-toulon-ce-que-l-on-sait-du-plan-prevu-par-hakim-8682475.html|language=fr|newspaper=TF1}}</ref><ref name="washingtonpost">{{cite news|last1=Miller|first1=Greg|last2=Whitlock|first2=Craig|date=14 November 2015|title=Caught between internal and external terror threats, France struggles to cope|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/national-security/caught-between-internal-and-external-terror-threats-france-struggles-to-cope/2015/11/14/c5e9fab0-8b00-11e5-9a07-453018f9a0ec_story.html|newspaper=Washington Post}}</ref>
After being arrested, Marnissi told police that he initially wanted to fight in Syria, but since he was prohibited from leaving the country, he decided to "default" to an attack on French soil. Marnissi confirmed that his intended targets were "one or more naval bases in Toulon", home to most of France's naval force. "He was radicalized astonishingly quickly," [[Le Figaro]] quotes an informed [[source (journalism)|source]]. "After separating gradually from his family and inner circle, he found refuge in a silent attitude, then isolationism."<ref name="figaro"/>
