{{Infobox journal | title = Houston Journal of International Law | cover = | discipline = [[International Law]] | abbreviation = Houst. J. Int. Law | bluebook=Hous. J. Int'l L. | publisher = [[University of Houston Law Center]] | country = United States | frequency = Triannual | history = 1978–present | website = http://www.hjil.org | ISSN = 0194-1879 | OCLC = 53456119 | LCCN = 79643854 }} The '''''Houston Journal of International Law''''' ('''''HJIL''''') is a triannual student-edited [[law journal]] published by the [[University of Houston Law Center]]. It ranks among the top 28% of all international law journals and the top 28% of all law journals published worldwide.<ref>[http://lawlib.wlu.edu/LJ/index.aspx Law Journals: Submissions and Ranking, 2007–2014], [[Washington and Lee University School of Law|Washington & Lee University School of Law]].</ref> It was established in 1978.
